{"timestamp": "2025-12-05 11:40:21.161982", "event": "llm_end", "text": "Submission recorded.\n\nSummary of submission:\n- is_anomaly: true\n- faulty_devices: [\"switch_2\"]\n- root_cause_name: [\"southbound_port_mismatch\", \"p4_table_entry_missing\"]\n\nRationale (short):\n- Hosts configured correctly; switch_1 logs show forwarding out toward switch_2, but host_2 reports zero RX packets.\n- switch_2 logged \"JSON input file bloom_filter.json cannot be opened\" at startup (indicates missing initialization/state), and there were intermittent thrift/tool connection issues; these point to partial runtime/config failure and missing table/state entries.\n- Likely port mapping or southbound port mismatch and missing P4 table entries on switch_2 are the root causes preventing egress to host_2.\n\nIf you want, I can draft the exact troubleshooting steps to confirm and remediate (commands to check port mappings, tcpdump/tshark command examples, bmv2 table dump commands, and how to provide or fix the missing bloom_filter.json).", "generation_info": {"finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 2929, "output_tokens": 206, "total_tokens": 3135, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 2688}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 0}}}
